, shifting economic and national security policies, pervasive electronic media, and policy reform. Steering from the Centre details how chief executives in ten Western democracies have responded to governance challenges in the wake of reform ideas such as the New Public Management which stress deregulation and decentralization.This volume analyzes the extent to which the centre of government can retain political and administrative control when delivery of public services is increasingly done through networks, contacts, partnerships, and a host of other devolved arrangements. International in scope, Steering from the Centre covers the experiences of diverse countries and examines how various centralization/decentralization strategies have played out in these differing national and institutional contexts.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Aug 2021) 4aDISCOUNT-B. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh1 aBezes, Philippe, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDahlström, Carl, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDahlström, Carl, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aFleischer, Julia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHalligan, John, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJensen, Lotte, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKekkonen, Sirpa, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLe Lidec, Patrick, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPeters, B. Guy , eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aPeters, B. Guy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPierre, Jon, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPierre, Jon, eeditor.4edt